canonical:
  title: 懺經法席疏
  author: 權近
  language: lzh
  text: 慈悲懺法普開解脫之門幻化空身奄隔幽明之路玆勤敬禮敢丐提撕言念仙魂惟予皇辟戚聯宗室偏蒙寵渥之恩爵貴公侯尙篤謙恭之節常期百年之偕老何遽一日而永違由公禀受而然邪恐妾禍殃之致耳呼天踊地已無相見之期歸佛齋僧庶導超生之利爰當𣪁室特展熏筵倘玆營締之微格彼感通之速伏願蛻形骸之有漏直到天宮悟法性之無生證明佛果
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 懺經法席疏
  author: 權近
  language: lzh
  text: 慈悲懺法。普開解脫之門。幻化空身。奄隔幽明之路。玆勤敬禮。敢丐提撕。言念仙魂。惟予皇辟。戚聯宗室。偏蒙寵渥之恩。爵貴公侯。尙篤謙恭之節。常期百年之偕老。何遽一日而永違。由公禀受而然邪。恐妾禍殃之致耳。呼天踊地。已無相見之期。歸佛齋僧。庶導超生之利。爰當𣪁室。特展熏筵。倘玆營締之微。格彼感通之速。伏願蛻形骸之有漏。直到天宮。悟法性之無生。證明佛果。
korean:
  title: 참경 법석 소
  author: 권근
  language: kor
  text: 불교의 자비로운 참회법(懺悔法)은 널리 해탈(解脫)의 문을 열어 주셨는데, 헛 것[幻化]인 허무한 몸은 문득 저승과 이승의 길을 달리하였소. 이에 부처님께 부지런히 경례하며, 이끌어 주시기를 비나이다. 생각하오니, 가신 분은 나의 남편이었소. 종실(宗室)의 친척으로 특별히 은총을 받으셨고, 벼슬은 공후(公侯)로서 오히려 겸손하고 공손한 태도였습니다. 백년해로를 원하였더니 어찌 하루아침에 영원한 이별이었나이까. 공(公)의 타고난 명이 그 뿐인가. 아마도 첩의 재앙으로 그렇게 된 것입니다. 하늘에 부르짖고 땅에 굴러도 영영 만나 볼 수 없기에, 부처님께 귀의하고 스님에게 재를 드려, 좋은 곳에 나시도록 천도하나이다. 이에 찬실(𣪁室)을 당하여, 특별히 법회를 마련하오니, 설비한 것은 미미하오나 속히 감통하여 주소서. 엎드려 원하나이다. 유류(有漏)의 육신을 벗어나 바로 천궁으로 올라가시고, 생사(生死)가 없는 법성(法性)을 깨달아서 부처가 되어지이다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1160_010_0330&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Discourse on the Dharma Seat for the Confession Sutra
  author: Kwon Geun
  language: eng
  text: |-
    The Buddha's compassionate confession dissolves the barriers,
    Opening wide the gates of liberation.
    Yet this illusory form of flesh and bone
    Suddenly parts the roads of this world and the next.

    With reverent devotion I bow before the Three Jewels,
    Praying for guidance and awakening.
    I think of him who has gone before—
    My beloved, born of royal descent,
    Honored with rank among the highest,
    Yet ever humble in heart and bearing.
    We longed to grow old together through a hundred years,
    How could one dawn steal him from me forever?

    Was it written in his nature alone?
    Or have my failings brought this calamity upon us?
    Though I call out to heaven and prostrate upon earth,
    No meeting awaits in the world to come.
    So I take refuge in the Buddha's way,
    Offering alms to the monks for his salvation,
    That merit may guide him to a blessed realm.

    In this hour of deepest mourning,
    I prepare this humble dharma gathering.
    Though my offerings are meager,
    May they swiftly touch the hearts of the compassionate.

    I humbly pray:
    May he shed this body bound by karmic streams
    And rise directly to the celestial palace,
    May he awaken to the deathless nature of all dharmas
    And realize the fruition of Buddhahood.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: This is a memorial liturgy composed for a deceased member of the royal family, blending Confucian filial piety with Buddhist salvific hopes.
  - key: ''
    value: The reference to 'heaven' (天宮) reflects the syncretic beliefs of medieval Korea, where Buddhist cosmology coexisted with indigenous celestial concepts.
  - key: ''
    value: The speaker appears to be the widow, expressing both grief and self-blame, a common theme in East Asian elegiac literature.
